The Arulmigu Solaimalai Murugan Temple is a Hindu temple, located about 25 kilometres north of Madurai, atop a hill covered with dense forests. One of the six important abodes of the deity Murugan located in Tamil Nadu, it is close to the Vishnu temple of Alagar Kovil.The temple is maintained and administered by the Hindu Religious and Charitable Endowments Department of the Government of Tamil Nadu.